snippet.textDisplay:
I wrote about this a few years ago.

I feel as if once BMW really mastered the HMI - their iDrive system - they were scared to mess it up. They were the best, by far, at it's time. The best user experience and the safest.
But instead of plowing forward to continue to lead that space, they became content and were scared of change.

Some may argue that just lacking innovation on the HMI/Entertainment front couldn't do so much damage, but remember that the iDrive system is a core element of the car; many design decisions are based around it.

Also; people like "new". I did not see the logic in making gran coupe versions of the 3 and 4 series carry the same name except for adding gran coupe. A new name would of allowed them further expansion. The "gran coupe" stuff was just confusing. Also, one gran coupe is enough. Not much difference between the 3 and 4 to begin with.

Lastly, the exterior design of the 2 door coupes look almost identical to one 10 years old. Why buy a new one when literally nobody could even tell the difference. Same iDrive system, and same body for the most part.


--
snippet.textOriginal:
I wrote about this a few years ago.

I feel as if once BMW really mastered the HMI - their iDrive system - they were scared to mess it up. They were the best, by far, at it's time.  The best user experience and the safest. 
But instead of plowing forward to continue to lead that space, they became content and were scared of change.

Some may argue that just lacking innovation on the HMI/Entertainment front couldn't do so much damage, but remember that the iDrive system is a core element of the car; many design decisions are based around it. 

Also; people like "new". I did not see the logic in making gran coupe versions of the 3 and 4 series carry the same name except for adding gran coupe. A new name would of allowed them further expansion. The "gran coupe" stuff was just confusing. Also, one gran coupe is enough. Not much difference between the 3 and 4 to begin with.

Lastly, the exterior design of the 2 door coupes look almost identical to one 10 years old. Why buy a new one when literally nobody could even tell the difference. Same iDrive system, and same body for the most part.
